title: Louisa Van Velsor Whitman to Walt Whitman, 30 October [1867]
text: 30 Oct 67wensdayWednesdayWalteri have got the letter and 5 all safe this time i began to feel uneasy but it all right i think walt if you put them in the post office yourself they will come safe it is very strange about the other i dontdon't know how to live here this winter there is two families up stairs the dirtiest and every thing else that can be pictedpicked up i am about the same walter i dontdon't feel any worse and sometimes i feel better i am taking the medicine yet mat is here and sis they are well she has got a letter from Jeff i will write all about every thing next time walter dear i will be glad to get OconersO'Connor's book walt doodo you take the eagleEagle this is out of it good biewalt Louisa Van Velsor Whitman to Walt Whitman, 30 October [1867]
